summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions on Sudan, notes the Sudan Government's request to terminate UNMIS on 9 July. Reaffirming commitment to Sudan's sovereignty and peace, it:

1. Decides to withdraw UNMIS effective 11 July 2011;

2. Calls for complete withdrawal of personnel by 31 August 2011;

3. Requests transfer of staff, equipment, and assets to UNMISS and UNISFA;

4. Urges Sudan to respect the Status of Forces Agreement, guaranteeing UN access, movement, and export of equipment;

5. Emphasizes a smooth transition to UNISFA and UNMISS;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to consult on options for UN support to new security arrangements in Blue Nile and Southern Kordofan States;

7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
